verses.verse: A Song <S%H7892><s%> of degrees. <S%H4609><s%> Unto <S%H413><s%> thee lift I up <S%H5375><s%> <S%H853><s%> mine eyes, <S%H5869><s%> O thou that dwellest <S%H3427><s%> in the heavens. <S%H8064><s%>

Behold, <S%H2009><s%> as the eyes <S%H5869><s%> of servants <S%H5650><s%> look unto <S%H413><s%> the hand <S%H3027><s%> of their masters, <S%H113><s%> and as the eyes <S%H5869><s%> of a maiden <S%H8198><s%> unto <S%H413><s%> the hand <S%H3027><s%> of her mistress; <S%H1404><s%> so <S%H3651><s%> our eyes <S%H5869><s%> wait upon <S%H413><s%> the LORD <S%H3068><s%> our God, <S%H430><s%> until <S%H5704><s%> that he have mercy upon <S%H7945><s%> <S%H2603><s%> us.
Have mercy upon <S%H2603><s%> us, O LORD, <S%H3068><s%> have mercy upon <S%H2603><s%> us: for <S%H3588><s%> we are exceedingly <S%H7227><s%> filled <S%H7646><s%> with contempt. <S%H937><s%>

Our soul <S%H5315><s%> is exceedingly <S%H7227><s%> filled <S%H7646><s%> with the scorning <S%H3933><s%> of those that are at ease, <S%H7600><s%> and with the contempt <S%H937><s%> of the proud. <S%H1349><s%>
